HEADWORD: Extradictionary
<hw>Ex`tra*dic"tion*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>extra-</ets> + L. <ets>dictio</ets> a saying. See
<er>Diction</er>.]</ety> <def>Consisting not in words, but in
realities.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of these <qex>extradictionary</qex> and real fallacies, Aristotle
and logicians make in number six.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extraditable</ent>⟦br⟧
